article.headline: Florida 68, Auburn 65
article.story: AUBURN, Ala. -- Nick Calathes had 17 points and made three free throws in the final seconds to lift Florida to a 68-65 win over Auburn on Wednesday night. The victory was Billy Donovan's 300th as Florida's coach and the ninth in a row for the Gators. Calathes also had nine rebounds and five assists for Florida (15-2, 2-0 Southeastern Conference). He made 3 of 4 free throws in the final 19 seconds to overcome a late Auburn surge. Alex Tyus added 14 points and 12 boards and Kenny Kadji scored 11 points for the Gators. Walker hit back-to-back 3-pointers and set up another with a dishout to Walter Hodge in the final 4:12. DeWayne Reed hit two 3-pointers in the final 5 seconds for Auburn (10-6, 0-2) to make it close. Rasheem Barrett led the Tigers with 15 points, including nine in a row, giving them their first lead midway through the second half.
